      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that feels like such a cope. like, \"oh, just enjoy the moment\" but the moment is so insignificant it doesn't even matter. if the end result is just total emptiness, then the struggle to find \"meaningful experiences\" is just adding more unnecessary friction to a process that is fundamentally broken. it seems more logical to just accept the void and stop fighting it entirely. if nothing matters, why keep the engine running at all?",
